<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-04T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10027a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-04T19:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1185. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>, War Trade
                                Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 1160. <persName>Frothingham</persName>. What progress has been
                                made in matter urging adoption effective enemy trade restrictions by
                                Portugal? Portuguese in certain South American countries are
                                cloaking enemy <pb facs="0221" n="1055" xml:id="pg_1055"/> trade.
                                Our representatives advise only effective remedy is adoption of full
                                enemy trade restrictions by Portugal. This should be discussed with
                                British in furtherance of early decision concerning publishing enemy
                                trading list for Portugal which was subject of communications from
                                you several months ago. French representative, Washington, has been
                                instructed by his Government to ask cooperation United States in
                                obtaining British assistance urging Portugal to act immediately.
                                Await your advice as to situation. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>